The evidence with the title 'Newt Gingrich addresses ethics violations charges | huffpost ' says Jan 22, 2012  ...  ... Newt Gingrich found himself facing questions around the ethics charges brought against him during his tenure as speaker of the House . Eighty-four charges of ethics violations were filed against Gingrich in 1997, resulting in his being reprimanded by the House Of Representatives and fined $300,000. 
